.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-60 Cashu wallet state management over Nostr. A Cashu wallet
stores its state in relay events so it is accessible across applications.
.PP
Four event kinds are involved:
.IP "\fBkind 17375\fR \- Wallet event (replaceable). Contains NIP\-44 encrypted wallet private key and trusted mint URLs. The private key is used exclusively for P2PK ecash operations and MUST NOT be the user\*(Aqs Nostr private key." 4
.IX Item "kind 17375 - Wallet event (replaceable). Contains NIP-44 encrypted wallet private key and trusted mint URLs. The private key is used exclusively for P2PK ecash operations and MUST NOT be the user's Nostr private key."
.PD 0
.IP "\fBkind 7375\fR \- Token event. Contains NIP\-44 encrypted unspent Cashu proofs. Multiple token events can exist per mint, and each can hold multiple proofs. When proofs are spent, the token event MUST be NIP\-09 deleted and unspent proofs rolled over into a new token event." 4
.IX Item "kind 7375 - Token event. Contains NIP-44 encrypted unspent Cashu proofs. Multiple token events can exist per mint, and each can hold multiple proofs. When proofs are spent, the token event MUST be NIP-09 deleted and unspent proofs rolled over into a new token event."
.ie n .IP "\fBkind 7376\fR \- Spending history event. Records balance changes with direction, amount, and event references. Clients SHOULD publish these when the balance changes. The ""e"" tags with ""redeemed"" markers SHOULD be left unencrypted in public tags." 4
.el .IP "\fBkind 7376\fR \- Spending history event. Records balance changes with direction, amount, and event references. Clients SHOULD publish these when the balance changes. The \f(CWe\fR tags with \f(CWredeemed\fR markers SHOULD be left unencrypted in public tags." 4
.IX Item "kind 7376 - Spending history event. Records balance changes with direction, amount, and event references. Clients SHOULD publish these when the balance changes. The e tags with redeemed markers SHOULD be left unencrypted in public tags."
.IP "\fBkind 7374\fR \- Quote redemption event (optional). Tracks mint quote IDs with a NIP\-40 expiration of approximately two weeks. Application developers SHOULD prefer local state when possible." 4
.IX Item "kind 7374 - Quote redemption event (optional). Tracks mint quote IDs with a NIP-40 expiration of approximately two weeks. Application developers SHOULD prefer local state when possible."
.PD
.PP
All content fields are NIP\-44 encrypted. This module accepts pre\-encrypted
content for event creation and provides helper methods to build the plaintext
payloads and parse decrypted content.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 1
\&    my $w = Net::Nostr::Wallet\->new(%fields);
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Wallet\*(C'\fR object. Typically returned by
"from_event" or the \f(CW\*(C`parse_*\*(C'\fR methods; calling \f(CW\*(C`new\*(C'\fR directly is
useful for testing. Croaks on unknown arguments.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS wallet_event
.IX Subsection "wallet_event"
.Vb 4
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Wallet\->wallet_event(
\&        pubkey  => $hex_pubkey,
\&        content => $encrypted,  # NIP\-44 encrypted wallet_content()
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 17375 wallet Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR
are required. Tags are always empty (all data is in the encrypted content).
.SS token_event
.IX Subsection "token_event"
.Vb 4
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Wallet\->token_event(
\&        pubkey  => $hex_pubkey,
\&        content => $encrypted,  # NIP\-44 encrypted token_content()
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 7375 token Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR
are required. Tags are always empty.
.SS history_event
.IX Subsection "history_event"
.Vb 5
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Wallet\->history_event(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,
\&        content      => $encrypted,  # NIP\-44 encrypted history_content()
\&        redeemed_ids => [[$event_id, $relay_hint], ...],  # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 7376 spending history Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR and
\&\f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR are required. \f(CW\*(C`redeemed_ids\*(C'\fR is an optional arrayref of
\&\f(CW\*(C`[$event_id, $relay_hint]\*(C'\fR pairs that become unencrypted \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags with
the \f(CW\*(C`redeemed\*(C'\fR marker.
.SS quote_event
.IX Subsection "quote_event"
.Vb 6
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Wallet\->quote_event(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        content    => $encrypted,  # NIP\-44 encrypted quote ID
\&        mint_url   => \*(Aqhttps://mint\*(Aq,
\&        expiration => $timestamp,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 7374 quote redemption Net::Nostr::Event. All parameters
are required. The expiration should be approximately two weeks (the maximum
time a Lightning payment may be in\-flight).
.SS delete_token
.IX Subsection "delete_token"
.Vb 4
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Wallet\->delete_token(
\&        pubkey    => $hex_pubkey,
\&        event_ids => [$token_event_id, ...],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 5 NIP\-09 deletion Net::Nostr::Event for spent token
events. Includes \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags for each token and a \f(CW\*(C`["k", "7375"]\*(C'\fR tag
as required by the spec to allow easy filtering.
.SS wallet_content
.IX Subsection "wallet_content"
.Vb 4
\&    my $plaintext = Net::Nostr::Wallet\->wallet_content(
\&        privkey => $hex_privkey,
\&        mints   => [\*(Aqhttps://mint1\*(Aq, \*(Aqhttps://mint2\*(Aq],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Builds the JSON plaintext for a wallet event\*(Aqs content. Returns a JSON
string ready for NIP\-44 encryption. \f(CW\*(C`privkey\*(C'\fR is the P2PK private key
(not the user\*(Aqs Nostr key). \f(CW\*(C`mints\*(C'\fR must have at least one entry.
.SS token_content
.IX Subsection "token_content"
.Vb 6
\&    my $plaintext = Net::Nostr::Wallet\->token_content(
\&        mint   => \*(Aqhttps://mint\*(Aq,
\&        proofs => [{ id => \*(Aq...\*(Aq, amount => 1, secret => \*(Aq...\*(Aq, C => \*(Aq...\*(Aq }],
\&        unit   => \*(Aqsat\*(Aq,             # optional, default \*(Aqsat\*(Aq
\&        del    => [\*(Aqold\-token\-id\*(Aq],  # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Builds the JSON plaintext for a token event\*(Aqs content. \f(CW\*(C`mint\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`proofs\*(C'\fR
are required. \f(CW\*(C`unit\*(C'\fR defaults to \f(CW\*(C`sat\*(C'\fR. \f(CW\*(C`del\*(C'\fR lists token event IDs that
were destroyed in creating this token (assists with state transitions).
.SS history_content
.IX Subsection "history_content"
.Vb 9
\&    my $plaintext = Net::Nostr::Wallet\->history_content(
\&        direction => \*(Aqout\*(Aq,          # \*(Aqin\*(Aq or \*(Aqout\*(Aq
\&        amount    => \*(Aq4\*(Aq,
\&        unit      => \*(Aqsat\*(Aq,          # optional, default \*(Aqsat\*(Aq
\&        e_tags    => [
\&            [$event_id, $relay_hint, $marker],
\&            ...
\&        ],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Builds the JSON plaintext for a history event\*(Aqs content. \f(CW\*(C`direction\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`amount\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`e_tags\*(C'\fR are required. Each \f(CW\*(C`e_tag\*(C'\fR entry is an arrayref
of \f(CW\*(C`[$event_id, $relay_hint, $marker]\*(C'\fR where marker is \f(CW\*(C`created\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`destroyed\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`redeemed\*(C'\fR.
.SS parse_wallet_content
.IX Subsection "parse_wallet_content"
.Vb 3
\&    my $wallet = Net::Nostr::Wallet\->parse_wallet_content($decrypted_json);
\&    say $wallet\->privkey;
\&    say join \*(Aq, \*(Aq, @{$wallet\->mints};
.Ve
.PP
Parses decrypted wallet content into a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Wallet\*(C'\fR object.
.SS parse_token_content
.IX Subsection "parse_token_content"
.Vb 5
\&    my $token = Net::Nostr::Wallet\->parse_token_content($decrypted_json);
\&    say $token\->mint;
\&    say $token\->unit;
\&    say scalar @{$token\->proofs};
\&    say join \*(Aq, \*(Aq, @{$token\->del};
.Ve
.PP
Parses decrypted token content into a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Wallet\*(C'\fR object.
\&\f(CW\*(C`unit\*(C'\fR defaults to \f(CW\*(C`sat\*(C'\fR if not present. \f(CW\*(C`del\*(C'\fR defaults to an empty
arrayref.
.SS parse_history_content
.IX Subsection "parse_history_content"
.Vb 7
\&    my $hist = Net::Nostr::Wallet\->parse_history_content($decrypted_json);
\&    say $hist\->direction;  # \*(Aqin\*(Aq or \*(Aqout\*(Aq
\&    say $hist\->amount;
\&    say $hist\->unit;
\&    for my $e (@{$hist\->e_tags}) {
\&        say "$e\->[0] ($e\->[2])";  # event_id (marker)
\&    }
.Ve
.PP
Parses decrypted history content into a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Wallet\*(C'\fR object.
\&\f(CW\*(C`unit\*(C'\fR defaults to \f(CW\*(C`sat\*(C'\fR if not present.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $parsed = Net::Nostr::Wallet\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 17375, 7375, 7376, or 7374 event into a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Wallet\*(C'\fR
object using only public (unencrypted) tags. For kind 7376, extracts
\&\f(CW\*(C`redeemed_ids\*(C'\fR from public \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags. For kind 7374, extracts \f(CW\*(C`mint_url\*(C'\fR
and \f(CW\*(C`expiration\*(C'\fR. Returns \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR for unrecognized kinds.
.PP
To access encrypted content, first decrypt the event\*(Aqs content with NIP\-44,
then use "parse_wallet_content", "parse_token_content", or
"parse_history_content".
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::Wallet\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates a wallet\-related event. Croaks on invalid structure. For kinds
17375, 7375, and 7376, validation passes since content is encrypted and
public tags are optional. For kind 7374, requires \f(CW\*(C`expiration\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`mint\*(C'\fR
tags.
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
Available on objects returned by "from_event" and the \f(CW\*(C`parse_*\*(C'\fR methods.
Which accessors contain data depends on what was parsed.
.SS privkey
.IX Subsection "privkey"
The P2PK private key (from parsed wallet content).
.SS mints
.IX Subsection "mints"
Arrayref of mint URLs (from parsed wallet content).
.SS mint
.IX Subsection "mint"
The mint URL (from parsed token content).
.SS unit
.IX Subsection "unit"
The base unit, e.g. \f(CW\*(C`sat\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`usd\*(C'\fR (from parsed token or history content).
.SS proofs
.IX Subsection "proofs"
Arrayref of proof hashrefs (from parsed token content).
.SS del
.IX Subsection "del"
Arrayref of destroyed token event IDs (from parsed token content).
.SS direction
.IX Subsection "direction"
Transaction direction: \f(CW\*(C`in\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`out\*(C'\fR (from parsed history content).
.SS amount
.IX Subsection "amount"
Transaction amount as string (from parsed history content).
.SS e_tags
.IX Subsection "e_tags"
Arrayref of \f(CW\*(C`[$event_id, $relay_hint, $marker]\*(C'\fR entries (from parsed
history content).
.SS redeemed_ids
.IX Subsection "redeemed_ids"
Arrayref of redeemed nutzap event IDs from public \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags (from
"from_event" on kind 7376).
.SS mint_url
.IX Subsection "mint_url"
The mint URL from the \f(CW\*(C`mint\*(C'\fR tag (from "from_event" on kind 7374).
.SS expiration
.IX Subsection "expiration"
The expiration timestamp (from "from_event" on kind 7374).
